SIMPLE: tittle-tattle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tittle-tattle
<hw>Tit"tle-tat`tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A
reduplication of <ets>tattle</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Idle,
trifling talk; empty prattle.</def> <rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An idle, trifling talker; a gossip.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Tatler.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tittle-tattle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tittle-tattle
<hw>Tit"tle-tat`tle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To talk idly; to
prate.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tittle-tattling</ent>⟦br⟧
